      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/ecb155/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2024-04-20T22:12:47.288Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hi, I understand this is not a configuration you are used to but maybe you can give me some help anyway. I use a Schwinn IC4 stationary bike with Tempo Power Meters and use a device called Smartspin2K which turns spin bikes into smart trainers. My setup works perfectly in Zwift, TrainerRoad, Rouvy, etc. I just started using TD because I like it better than TR (not to mention the cost)</p>\n<p>Anyway, When I am doing a workout, ERG works fine from the beginning but somewhere in the workout a few minutes into the ride ERG mode stops working and the only option available is slope mode. Once it is in slope mode ERG mode is greyed out for the rest of the ride. Also if I start a ride and manually go to slope mode I can never go back to ERG mode. The only way to get ERG mode to turn on again is exit the workoutt and start again.</p>\n<p>The only other thing that may be a factor is I do have 2 or 3 dropouts in a ride but they are very brief and it comes right back up.</p>\n<p>Is there any setting or anything I should look at to help with this.? Otherwise I love the app and the training plans!</p>\n<p>Schwinn IC4 bike with Smartspin2K<br>\nSamsung Android tablet</p>\n<p>Thank You</p>",
